<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Jan Lukava von Oberlukawitz, Burggraf zu Taus, und Taus</head><p>Der Rat dankt wegen der Gefangenen zu Taus und kündigt Hans Neustetter, Diener der Stadt, an.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_178" id="89r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_178_r1l1">Jan von <expan>Ob<ex>er</ex>n</expan> Lukawıcʒ </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l2"><expan>Burggraf<ex>en</ex></expan> ʒu Tawſt </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_178_r1l3"><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> Jan als Jr vns <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von der <expan>gefang<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> ʒu Tawſt etc </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l4">das <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wır wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> . vnd <expan>dank<ex>en</ex></expan> eẅch <expan>fleıſſıkl<ex>ich</ex></expan> . <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>s</expan> guten <expan>wıll<ex>e</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l5">den Jr vns in den <expan>ſach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> beweıſet / Vnd <expan>bıtt<ex>en</ex></expan> eẅch . daʒ Jr hinfür <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l6">fleıſſ vnd ernſt darcʒu tun wellet / als wır eẅch getrawen Vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l7">als wır eẅch vnd den <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>n</expan> . in <expan>ſölıch<ex>en</ex></expan> vnd <expan>mer<ex>er</ex>n</expan> <expan>ſache<ex>n</ex></expan> . bey vns <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l8">tun <expan>wölt<ex>en</ex></expan> ob eẅch des not beſchehe Vnd was <expan>dıſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>dıen<ex>er</ex></expan> Hanns </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l9"><expan>Neẅſtett<ex>er</ex></expan> ʒu <expan>dıſ<ex>em</ex></expan> mal in den <expan>ſach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> müntlıch an eẅch werbe . das </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l11">wellet Jm 
<add><ab facs="#facs_178_r1l10"><expan>gencʒl<ex>ich</ex></expan> </ab></add> <expan>gelawbe<ex>n</ex></expan> vnd gütlıch <expan>darınn<ex>en</ex></expan> befolhen <expan>laſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> ſein vnd <expan>fertig<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l12">das <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wır <expan>ſunderl<ex>ich</ex></expan> <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> vmb eẅch <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dıenen</expan> / <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi> poſt </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_178_r1l13">bonifacij </ab>
</div>
<div type="similiter"><ab facs="#facs_178_r1l14"><expan>Jt<ex>em</ex></expan> der Stat ʒu Tawſt <expan>ſı<ex>mi</ex>l<ex>ite</ex>r</expan> <expan>mutat<ex>is</ex></expan> <expan>muta<ex>n</ex>dıs</expan> </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_178" id="89r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Jan von <expan>Ob<ex>er</ex>n</expan> Lukawicz,
                            <expan>burggraf<ex>en</ex></expan> zu Tawst </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> Jan, als ir uns
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von der
                                <expan>gefang<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> zu Tawst etc., das
                            <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan>
                        und <expan>dank<ex>en</ex></expan> ewch <expan>fleissikl<ex>ich</ex></expan>
<expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> guten <expan>will<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, den ir
                        uns in den <expan>sach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> beweiset. Und
                                <expan>bitt<ex>en</ex></expan> ewch, daz ir hinfür
                                <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> fleiss und ernst darczu tun wellet, als
                        wir ewch getrawen und als wir ewch und den <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> in
                                <expan>sölich<ex>en</ex></expan> und <expan>mer<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>sache<ex>n</ex></expan> bey uns <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tun
                                <expan>wölt<ex>en,</ex></expan> ob ewch des not beschehe; und was
                                <expan>dis<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>dien<ex>er</ex></expan> Hanns <expan>Newstett<ex>er</ex></expan> zu
                                <expan>dis<ex>em</ex></expan> mal in den
                            <expan>sach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> müntlich an ewch werbe, das wellet im
                                    <add><expan>genczl<ex>ich</ex></expan></add>
<expan>gelawbe<ex>n</ex></expan> und gütlich
                            <expan>darinn<ex>en</ex></expan> befolhen <expan>lass<ex>en</ex></expan>
                        sein und <expan>fertig<ex>en</ex></expan>. Das
                            <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir <expan>sunderl<ex>ich</ex></expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> umb ewch <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dienen</expan>.
                                <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> v<hi rend="sup">a</hi> post Bonifacii. </ab>
</div>
<div type="similiter">
<ab><expan>It<ex>em</ex></expan> der stat zu Tawst
                                <expan>si<ex>mi</ex>l<ex>ite</ex>r</expan>
<expan>mutat<ex>is</ex></expan>
<expan>muta<ex>n</ex>dis.</expan>
</ab>
</div>
</div></body>
